From: Ashish Kumar Singh <ashishkmr472@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 13:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wayland/outputs: skip output update when monitor has no logical_monitor

meta_monitor_get_logical_monitor() can legitimately return NULL: see
meta_monitor_update_outputs() in src/backends/meta-monitor.c, which calls
meta_monitor_set_logical_monitor (monitor, NULL) on entry and only re-assigns
the logical monitor when the rebuild completes.

The Wayland-side on_monitors_changing handler (hooked to MONITORS_CHANGING
emitted by meta_monitor_manager_notify_monitors_changed) fires from inside
meta_monitor_manager_rebuild. It iterates monitors and calls send_output_events
which dereferences the (potentially NULL) logical_monitor without checking,
producing a SIGSEGV in meta_logical_monitor_get_layout.

This is reliably reproducible with hot-pluggable VR HMDs whose EDID flaps under
load (HP Reverb G2 on NVIDIA proprietary, where DP link-train retries cause
nvidia-modeset to re-read EDID multiple times per second; each re-read triggers
a kernel-side hotplug -> udev event -> mutter rebuild -> race window).

The upstream pattern is shown in meta_monitor_manager_get_monitor_for_connector
at src/backends/meta-monitor-manager.c:4205-4211 -- guard with
meta_monitor_is_active (monitor) (or NULL-check the logical_monitor pointer)
before dereferencing the logical_monitor side-band.

Apply the same pattern here:
  - send_output_events:               early return if logical_monitor NULL
  - send_xdg_output_events:           early return if logical_monitor NULL
  - meta_wayland_output_set_monitor:  don't overwrite cached layout/transform
                                       with zeros; defer until rebuild completes

The bind_output debug print (only used with WITH_VERBOSE_MODE) is unchanged
because it prints logical_monitor as %p which is NULL-safe.

When rebuild completes, meta_monitor_manager_notify_monitors_changed fires
the signal chain again, and these handlers re-run with a valid logical_monitor.

Forwarded: no
Last-Update: 2026-05-20
Index: mutter-50.1/src/wayland/meta-wayland-outputs.c
===================================================================
--- mutter-50.1.orig/src/wayland/meta-wayland-outputs.c
+++ mutter-50.1/src/wayland/meta-wayland-outputs.c
@@ -250,6 +250,14 @@ send_output_events (struct wl_resource *
   int old_mode_width, old_mode_height;
   gboolean need_done = FALSE;
 
+  /* A rebuild can transiently leave the monitor with no logical_monitor
+   * (see meta_monitor_update_outputs() in meta-monitor.c). Skip sending
+   * stale/garbage geometry to clients -- the next rebuild emission will
+   * fire this handler again once the logical monitor is reassigned.
+   */
+  if (!logical_monitor)
+    return;
+
   layout = meta_logical_monitor_get_layout (logical_monitor);
   old_layout = wayland_output->layout;
 
@@ -446,6 +454,16 @@ meta_wayland_output_set_monitor (MetaWay
   wayland_output->monitor = monitor;
 
   logical_monitor = meta_monitor_get_logical_monitor (monitor);
+
+  /* During a monitor-manager rebuild the monitor can be transiently
+   * disassociated from its logical_monitor (see meta_monitor_update_outputs
+   * in meta-monitor.c). Don't overwrite the cached layout/transform/scale
+   * with garbage values -- defer until rebuild completes and this is called
+   * again with a valid logical_monitor.
+   */
+  if (!logical_monitor)
+    return;
+
   wayland_output->layout = meta_logical_monitor_get_layout (logical_monitor);
   wayland_output->subpixel_order = meta_monitor_get_subpixel_order (monitor);
   wayland_output->transform =
@@ -706,6 +724,12 @@ send_xdg_output_events (struct wl_resour
   MtkRectangle old_layout;
   gboolean need_done = FALSE;
 
+  /* See send_output_events: a monitor-manager rebuild can transiently
+   * leave the monitor without a logical_monitor. Skip stale geometry.
+   */
+  if (!logical_monitor)
+    return;
+
   layout = meta_logical_monitor_get_layout (logical_monitor);
   old_layout = wayland_output->layout;
 
